  "text": "Completed implementation of Amp provider for Rulesets project with full success criteria met:\n\n**What was built:**\n- Complete Amp provider implementation outputting to AGENT.md\n- Comprehensive test suite (9 passing tests)\n- Full integration with provider registry\n- Complete documentation and usage examples\n- Working example demonstrating usage\n\n**Architecture decisions:**\n- Used 'agent' type for AI assistant category\n- Chose 'preserve' file naming strategy for fixed AGENT.md filename\n- Set 10MB max file size (reasonable for AI assistant rules)\n- Disabled XML support (Amp doesn't need complexity)\n- Focused on pure Markdown output for simplicity\n\n**Files created/modified:**\n- packages/core/src/providers/amp-provider.ts (main implementation)\n- packages/core/src/providers/__tests__/amp-provider.spec.ts (tests)\n- packages/core/examples/amp-example.ts (usage example)\n- docs/plugins/amp/rules-use.md (comprehensive documentation)\n- Multiple registry integration files (index.ts, brands.ts, provider.ts)\n\n**Testing strategy:**\n- Used bun:test framework (not vitest due to project inconsistencies)\n- Covered all provider interface methods\n- Tested configuration schema validation\n- Verified registry integration\n- Validated provider capabilities\n\n**Success metrics achieved:**\n✅ Provider compiles without errors\n✅ Outputs to AGENT.md (singular as specified)\n✅ Integrates with existing provider registry\n✅ Passes all type checks\n✅ Comprehensive test coverage\n✅ Clean, simple implementation\n✅ Follows established patterns\n\nThe implementation is production-ready and follows all project conventions. User can now use 'amp' as a provider in their Rulesets configuration.",
